Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  238
Edition:
Quote:  Evenness of fleece is always to be preferred to a fleece which is particularly good on one part of the carcase and weak on another part. Avoid "tippy" wool as much as possible.
